{
    "problem": "Compute\n\\[\\sum_{n = 1}^\\infty \\frac{1}{n(n + 2)}.\\]",
    "level": "Level 3",
    "type": "Intermediate Algebra",
    "solution": "By partial fractions,\n\\[\\frac{1}{n(n + 2)} = \\frac{1/2}{n} - \\frac{1/2}{n + 2}.\\]Hence,\n\\begin{align*}\n\\sum_{n = 1}^\\infty \\frac{1}{n(n + 2)} &= \\left( \\frac{1/2}{1} - \\frac{1/2}{3} \\right) + \\left( \\frac{1/2}{2} - \\frac{1/2}{4} \\right) + \\left( \\frac{1/2}{3} - \\frac{1/2}{5} \\right) + \\left( \\frac{1/2}{4} - \\frac{1/2}{6} \\right) + \\dotsb \\\\\n&= \\frac{1/2}{1} + \\frac{1/2}{2} \\\\\n&= \\boxed{\\frac{3}{4}}.\n\\end{align*}"
}